==== ENTRY 1 ====
HEADWORD: Headlight
<hw>Head"light`</hw> <pr>(h⟦ecr⟧d"l⟦imac⟧t`)</pr>, <pos>n.</pos>
<fld>(Engin.)</fld> <def>A light, with a powerful reflector, placed at
the front of a vehicle such as an automobile, truck, locomotive etc., to
throw light on the road or track ahead of the vehicle at night, or in
going through a dark tunnel; a <altname>headlamp</altname>.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source> <source>+PJC</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Headline</ent>⟦br⟧
